The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Banker shot 

 Moscow, Sept. 14 (Reuters): A Russian central banker who fought to clean up his countrys murky banking system died early today from gunshot wounds after being ambushed by assassins in what police said was a contract hit.

 Andrei Kozlov, 41, a respected first deputy chairman of the Central Bank, had led a fearless campaign to close banks suspected of involvement in money laundering. Gunmen fired on him as he left a football match . Kozlov fell to the ground bleeding from the head and chest and was rushed to hospital, where he died a few hours later. 




